Fix long log entries when skippable functions return large objects

Attempt fix at @skippable tasks running when constants within changed

We can never detect 100% of changes; weaknesses
     calling out to another function and that function's source changes
     you modify a constant within the function and it remains the same
     length in the source.

Workarounds:
   - Add a comment to your function somewhere where it needs it :)

    - If you want a function to re-run, chances are it either requires an input
    path or an output path. Quit hardcoding it as a constant and take it as
    a parameter; then you can just `$ touch input-file` or remove the output
    file.

Also update doc for skippable and add doc for improved errors.

This way you can copy-paste a variable name out of function declaration,
also less frustrating when coming from something like argparse.
